The article discusses the importance of the National Park System in the United States and the efforts being made to preserve and protect these natural wonders. President Joseph R. Biden Jr. launched the "America the Beautiful" initiative, which aims to conserve 30 percent of the country's lands and waters by 2030. The administration is investing over a billion dollars to restore national parks and public lands, combat climate change, and improve infrastructure within the parks. President Biden has also used executive authorities to protect and expand national monuments and ensure equal access to parks for all Americans. The article encourages people to take advantage of National Park Week and visit these cherished places.